bioghist.p:
From the time that he settled in Florence until his death in 1888, Jarves' primary interest was art. Not only was he responsible for amassing a valuable European art collection and transporting it to the United States, but he was also a contributor to the art scholarship of the time. He wrote several books, including: 
               Art Hints
             (1855); 
               Art Studies: The Old Masters of Italy
             (1861); 
               The Art Idea: Sculpture, Painting, and Architecture in America
             (1866); 
               Art Thoughts: The Experiences and Observations of an American Amateur in Europe
             (1876).
